<P>To all guild leaders - I know it's a difficult task, but I propose a more open line
of communication between the guilds on our server.  I have heard that it has been done
on other servers.  We, as the guild leaders, have the ability to encourage our members to
be productive members of the Everquest society.  If we pool our resources, we will be able

to have a louder voice when dealing with Verant, be able to hold larger events - like the
official EQ ones, but molded to our liking.  There are many possibilities, maybe a
guildleaders chat for planning events and an internet messageboard? I am keeping my hopes
to a minimum, because I know of the difficulty involved in coordinating this many people.
According to most of the information that I can find, there are around 100 active guilds
on the Solusek Ro server.  I am not so ambitious to think we can get them all together,
but I think few dozen can join together.  I will be contacting the guild leaders by email
and online over the next month to see what we can put together.</P>
